# Token efficiency and high-context warnings

## Model choice (monthly quota)

| Use | Model |
|-----|--------|
| Questions, explanations, quick lookups, short clarifications | Prefer **smaller / faster / cheaper** (non-Max unless needed) |
| Multi-file work, migrations, architecture, subtle cross-cutting bugs | Prefer **larger / Max / strongest** |

Remind the user to **pick the model in the chat/composer dropdown** before starting when scope is obvious; switch up if scope grows mid-thread.

## ~180k token threshold (heuristic)

There is **no** reliable pre-send token counter in Cursor. **Before** acting, estimate whether this turn (input + tool output) could approach or exceed **~180k tokens**.

**Warn first** (then proceed if the user confirms) when:

- Many large `@` references, whole folders, or repo-wide context.
- Very long pastes (logs, SQL dumps, JSON).
- The next step would read multiple huge files or run tools returning very large output.
- A **long thread** plus a request that re-processes the same material end-to-end.

**Say briefly:** high estimated token cost; suggest a **narrower `@`**, **new chat**, **splitting** the task, or **summarizing** first; ask to confirm before continuing.

**Skip** this warning for trivial one-line questions or when the user explicitly asks to skip.
